## Animation

### Generic Animation
Create animation to move and change the selected elements.

```javascript
//Syntax
$("selector").animate({parameters}, speed, callback);
```
<p data-height="355" data-theme-id="0" data-slug-hash="BPyemP" data-default-tab="html,result" data-user="mikelin2018" data-embed-version="2" data-pen-title="BPyemP" class="codepen">See the Pen <a href="https://codepen.io/mikelin2018/pen/BPyemP/">BPyemP</a> by Mike_Lin (<a href="https://codepen.io/mikelin2018">@mikelin2018</a>) on <a href="https://codepen.io">CodePen</a>.</p>
<script async src="https://static.codepen.io/assets/embed/ei.js"></script>

Note: 
1. {parameters} is a map of CSS for the element to move to.
2. [optional] "speed" is a speed of animation , can be written in text or in millisecond.
3. [optional] callback is a function to be called after the animation execute.
4. If more than one animation is called at the same time, or an animation is called before the previous animation ends, an animation queue will hold all of them and execute one by one. So, all animations will eventually be executed.

